res_0: The first Nobel Prize in Physics was awarded in 1901 to Wilhelm Conrad Röntgen, a German physicist, for his discovery of X-rays. Röntgen was awarded the Nobel Prize in Physics in 1901 for his work on the discovery of X-rays, which he made in 1895. He was awarded 150,782 Swedish kronor (SEK), which is equivalent to approximately 7,731,004 USD in December 2007.
